misconceptions.inferred_category_name: Assuming array indices are always valid (no input validation for N)
misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes the program will always have at least one student, so it is safe to access the last element of the arrays without checking N.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: In Java, arrays have fixed bounds and indexing is strictly checked at runtime. If N is 0, then computing numberOfStudents - 1 yields -1 and any attempt to access studentNames[-1] or studentScores[-1] will throw an ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException. The problem statement typically implies N >= 1, but the program itself does not enforce it.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: Runtime exception (ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException) if the user enters N = 0.
